# Development Rules - Master Reference

## 🚨 PRIMARY RULES

### 1. Use Context7 First (External Libraries)

**ALWAYS consult Context7 MCP server for up-to-date library documentation:**

```bash
"use context7 to get Next.js 15 App Router patterns"
"use context7 to implement shadcn/ui components"
"use context7 to configure Tailwind CSS v4"
"use context7 to implement Supabase authentication with @supabase/ssr"
```

### 2. Document in Repo (Never Git Loops)

**CRITICAL**: All documentation lives in `docs/` directory, NOT in git commits
- ✅ Update files directly in `docs/` folder
- ❌ NEVER create unnecessary commits just for documentation
- ✅ Keep working branches focused on implementation
- ✅ Document decisions and progress locally first
- ✅ Review and commit documentation with feature code

**Documentation Locations**:
- `docs/security/` - Security and encryption documentation
- `docs/development/` - Tasks, architecture, features
- `docs/product/` - Requirements and user guides
- Always update relevant README.md in each section

